Slice the @sweet potato{1} in half lengthways, then chop into 1cm half moons (no need to peel).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, lay the @British chicken breasts{2} flat in the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until the chicken is browned, ~{4-5%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the chicken is browned, add the sweet potato. Stir in the @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @dried oregano{1%sachet} and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, half the @chicken stock paste{20%grams}, half the mint and the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{200%ml} for the sauce to the chicken.

> See pantry for both amounts.

Stir well to combine. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat to medium.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{220%ml} for the bulgur into another large saucepan, stir in the remaining chicken stock paste and bring to the boil.

> See pantry for amount.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

When the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste the sauce and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the bulgur wheat between your #serving bowls{} and top with the pachamanca inspired chicken and sauce.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} and sprinkle with the remaining mint to finish. Enjoy!